      "message": "[🟡 Suggestions] Line 177: The activity counter can undercount during configuration changes because every onActivityStopped decrements, even when another activity has already started. If the counter is accidentally clamped to 0, background deactivation may run while the app is still visible. Android\u0027s recommended process foreground tracking also considers started/resumed ordering and configuration changes. Track activity identities or use ProcessLifecycleOwner so a single reordered stop cannot deactivate active accounts while the user is in the app.\n```suggestion\nProcessLifecycleOwner.get().lifecycle.addObserver(object : DefaultLifecycleObserver {\n    override fun onStart(owner: LifecycleOwner) {\n        backgroundHandler.removeCallbacks(deactivateRunnable)\n        Log.d(TAG, \"App came to foreground — reactivating accounts\")\n        mAccountService.restoreProxyAccountsAfterBackground()\n    }\n\n    override fun onStop(owner: LifecycleOwner) {\n        scheduleBackgroundDeactivation()\n    }\n})\n```",
