      "side": 1,
      "message": "The premise does not hold on this platform: the daemon runs in-process (JNI), and Account::active_ is runtime-only (bool active_ {true} in account.h, never serialized — only enabled/registered state is persisted to config). Process death therefore resets all accounts to active on reload: the in-memory set matches exactly the lifetime of the state it tracks. Persisting it would add I/O on every transition and a stale-reactivation risk for zero recovery benefit. Documented at the declaration in PS17.",
